cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with decoding linear block codes, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The proposed decoding method can have applications in communication networks, making this sub-category a likely fit. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions the use of multiple structurally diverse parity-check matrices, which can be seen as a network of sorts. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new iterative decoding algorithm, which falls under the purview of algorithms and data structures. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed decoding method compared to the maximum-likelihood decoder, which can be seen as a complexity analysis.
